    {
      "instruction": "<p>Strip your<strong> mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Add your <strong>mooli slaw mix</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half </strong>of the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>, <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>nuoc cham </strong>(save the rest for later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and set aside – this is your <strong>quick-pickled nuoc cham mooli slaw</strong></p>",
